Alright, so I don't know how many people have found this artist yet since he's very new and only just started posting content at the kickstart of the year, but this guy is like... a Maid Marian fanatic. Over two dozen pieces of her, and very well imitated from the original Disney film's line and color crew, along with Kahl's illustrations. Nearly all of the content is self-insertion with her, other characters from the film and his human OC, on the level of a 50-year old DeviantArt boomer with his head permanently stuck on that one plain Catholic vixen he saw at the theater as a kid, and it's remarkable. It's like something you'd find buried in an old Netscape website from the 90s or the archives of some famous furry like Schwartz or Tezuka.

There's an entire four paragraph long treatise written about her character on his Furaffinity account. He's even posting hilarious Terminator 2 Robert Patrick edits with Marian on his Twitter account, along with screenshots of RE4's Mercs mode with Wesker and some $20 model of her swapped over Ashley. I don't even know where to begin with what I'm seeing, but it's all wonderfully tasteful.
